## File Naming Patterns

> **Naming rules — apply to every file and folder in this vault:**
> 1. **Lowercase and kebab-case.** All descriptive words are lowercase, separated by hyphens. No spaces, no underscores, no camelCase. Email addresses embedded in filenames are exempt — use them verbatim since they are identifiers, not prose.
> 2. **Globally unique names.** Obsidian resolves `[[wikilinks]]` by filename alone — two files with the same name make all links ambiguous and break the connection graph. Always include the subject person's email in any file that relates to a person. Generic names like `action-items.md` or `development-plan.md` without an email suffix are forbidden.

### Person Profiles and Folders

Use the person's actual email address exactly as it is — whatever format their company uses:

```
<email>.md    ← profile file (one per person, globally unique)
<email>/      ← folder for that person's artifacts
```

Common email formats across companies:

| Format | Example |
|--------|---------|
| `firstname.lastname@company.com` | `alice.smith@acme.com` |
| `flastname@company.com` | `asmith@acme.com` |
| `firstname_lastname@company.com` | `alice_smith@acme.com` |
| `firstname@company.com` | `alice@acme.com` |
| `firstnamelastname@company.com` | `alicesmith@acme.com` |

The format does not matter — what matters is using the real email consistently. Never invent a format or normalize it; use exactly what the person uses to log in.

### Meeting Notes
```
YYYY-MM-DD-<short-description>.md
```
Meeting notes are tied to a moment in time and a specific folder context, so the date + description is usually sufficient. When a meeting involves a specific person and might be linked from their profile, include their email:
```
YYYY-MM-DD-<description>-<email>.md
```
Examples:
- `2026-03-12-engineering-managers-ai-discussion.md`
- `2026-01-30-monthly-team-sync.md`

### 1-on-1 Notes
```
YYYY-MM-DD-1on1-<email>.md
```
External tools (e.g. Granola) often auto-generate display-name variants like `2026-03-24-Alice _ You - Topic.md`. Always rename to the kebab-case + email pattern before filing.

Examples:
- `2026-01-30-1on1-alice.smith@company.com.md`
- `2026-03-24-1on1-asmith@acme.com.md`

