## People Organization

All people — direct reports, stakeholders, peers — are identified by their email address. The email is a stable, unique key that works across folders, filenames, and note cross-references regardless of name changes or role changes.

Use the email exactly as it is — do not normalize or invent a format. If someone's address is `asmith@acme.com`, that is their identifier, not `alice.smith@acme.com`. Consistency matters more than readability.

The domain signals affiliation when managing across multiple companies or clients:
- `asmith@your-company.com` — your own organization
- `bjones@client.com` — client-side stakeholder
- `c.lee@partner.com` — partner or vendor contact

