## Claude Code Skills (workspace-local)

Skills live in `.claude/skills/` and extend Claude Code with domain-specific automation for this OS.

| Skill                    | What it does                                                                                                                                 |
| ------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `inbox-processor`        | Routes new meeting notes from `inbox/` to the correct folder, normalizes filenames, scaffolds missing person profiles, extracts action items |
| `presentation-generator` | Generates branded Marp presentations and exports to PPTX for a specific client or company style                                              |
| `monthly-feedback`       | Sends outbound peer feedback requests, captures replies, and generates per-person digest summaries for 1-on-1 notes                          |
| `objective-creator`      | Guided conversation that produces SMART performance objectives aligned to your company's review format                                       |

To adapt these skills to your context: copy the skill folder, update the SKILL.md with your company's naming conventions, branding, and process specifics.

